 sampling, add debug and error handling

SAMPLING:
- Remove @torch.compile from sample_tokens(). _filter_by_nucleus uses
  .any() and int() which cause graph breaks in torch dynamo; compiling
  produced unstable or failing graphs. Eager execution is reliable.
- Update docstrings: clarify parameters are tensors; note Gumbel-max
  trick for categorical sampling.

DEBUGGING:
- Set torch._dynamo.config.verbose = True in InferencePipeline.__init__
  to aid diagnosis of dynamo compilation issues during development.

ERROR HANDLING:
- Wrap _constrain_logits in try/except TypeError. On failure, print
  traceback to stderr with n_slots and processor state before re-raising.
  Helps debug logits processor signature mismatches (e.g. HF API changes).
- Wrap execute_step body in try/except TypeError. On failure, print
  traceback with prefill flag and n_slots before re-raising. Catches
  type errors in forward/sampling path for easier troubleshooting.

