Subject: [PATCH 46/53] fix(customized_vllm): address 5 CodeRabbit review
 issues in InferencePipeline
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Address CodeRabbit review issues #3–#7 from PR #858:

3. _constrain_logits() now processes each slot individually with its own
   token history instead of broadcasting slot[0]'s result. While ACE-Step
   typically shares a single processor instance, this handles the general
   case correctly.

4. execute_step() now calls logits_processor_update_state for every slot
   in the batch, not just slots[0]. This ensures all per-slot state
   machines advance correctly in both CFG and non-CFG paths.

5. Replace all print() calls with loguru logger (logger.info for KV cache
   stats, logger.error for TypeError diagnostics in _constrain_logits and
   execute_step).

6. _compiled_sizes now always includes max_bs via sorted(set([...] +
   [max_bs])), preventing StopIteration when the batch size equals
   max_num_seqs and doesn't align to a 16-boundary.

7. Wrap __init__ model loading in try/finally so torch.set_default_dtype
   and torch.set_default_device are always restored, even if model loading,
   warmup, KV provisioning, or CUDA graph capture raises an exception.

