 check and VRAM gate

Fix all 3 tests in llm_inference_enforce_eager_test.py that broke after
main added a Triton availability check and VRAM safety gate to
LLMHandler.initialize():

- Inject a fake triton module into sys.modules so the Triton import
  check inside initialize() succeeds (previously failed silently,
  causing enforce_eager=True regardless of flash_attn status, which
  made the test_enforce_eager_false_when_flash_attn_present assertion
  unreliable).

- Add get_gpu_memory_gb and torch.cuda.mem_get_info mocks returning
  16GB so the VRAM safety check (VRAM_SAFE_FREE_GB=2.0) passes and
  _initialize_5hz_lm_vllm is actually reached.

- Accept **_kw in fake_init_vllm so the new has_triton keyword
  argument does not raise TypeError (swallowed by the broad
  except Exception handler, causing captured dict to remain empty).

- Clean up sys.modules in a finally block using a sentinel to
  correctly distinguish "triton was absent" from "triton was None".

