From a45292ac96cb2bc08e30f3c1a072e2c65f61a704 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: fanzhang <4030914+tonyjohnvan@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 17 Mar 2026 19:02:35 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 53/53] fix(customized_vllm): reset ForwardState in finally
 block and add NaN guard on CFG logits

Two fixes in execute_step():

1. Move reset_context() into a finally block so thread-local
   ForwardState is always cleared even if the model forward pass
   throws. Previously a failed forward would leave stale attention
   metadata that could corrupt the next request.

2. Add torch.nan_to_num(cfg_logits, nan=-inf) after the CFG blend.
   When repetition penalty drives a token to -inf in both conditional
   and unconditional branches, the CFG formula produces NaN
   (-inf + scale * (-inf - -inf)). The guard replaces NaN with -inf
   so those tokens are safely excluded from sampling.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
